stimulus:
Introduction

Please sit comfortably with your face around 50cm from your screen during the experiment.

Click the button below to proceed.

The first part of the experiment will consist of two different sections:

  1. A practice section so you can get familiarized with the task you will be performing.
  2. A calibration section to ensure that everything is running correctly.

Please follow the instructions throughout each section carefully.

Press the button below to begin.

Tutorial

The video below demonstrates how the task will be performed.

  1. You will place your pinky on the A key
  2. Place your ring finger on the W key
  3. Place your middle finger on the E key
  4. Place your left thumb on the spacebar key
  5. Place your right index finger on the right arrow key

While still holding down with these fingers, simultaneously, when you see the GO!, tap the F key, repeatedly with your index finger as fast as you can!

  • Do not tap the F key until the GO! appears
  • Do not release the A, W, E, Spacebar, Right Arrow until prompted.

Click the button below to proceed.

Tutorial

The image below shows how your fingers should be placed on the keyboard throughout the task.

Click the button below to proceed.

Calibration

You will now begin the Calibration section of the experiment, which consists of three parts.
Press the button below to begin.

Calibration

Part 1

You will perform the same task as the practice section.

  1. You will place your pinky on the A key
  2. Place your ring finger on the W key
  3. Place your middle finger on the E key
  4. Place your left thumb on the spacebar key
  5. Place your right index finger on the right arrow key

While still holding down with these fingers, simultaneously, when you see the GO!, tap the F key, repeatedly with your index finger as fast as you can!


  • Do not tap the F key until the GO! appears
  • Do not release the A, W, E, Spacebar, Right Arrow until prompted.


Press the button below to proceed.

Calibration

Part 2

Get the red bar as high as possible with your taps!
  • Do not tap the F key until the GO! appears
  • Do not release the A, W, E, Spacebar, Right Arrow until prompted.

Click the button below to proceed.

Calibration

Part 3

Get the top of the red bar in the target area with your taps!
  • Do not tap the F key until the GO! appears
  • Do not release the A, W, E, Spacebar, Right Arrow until prompted.

Click the button below to proceed.
You will now enter the next phase of the experiment. Press the button below to proceed.

Trial Blocks

Part 1

During this next phase of the experiment, you will have the choice to skip or accept a trial.

You may skip the trial with the Left Arrow on your keyboard
or
You may accept a trial with the Right Arrow on your keyboard

If the trial is accepted, you may have to complete a tapping task:

  • The required target area will be shown in blue.
  • If the top of the red bar ends in the target area during the trial, you will receive the reward shown to you.

ⓘ Before the block begins, you will have a set of practice trials to familiarize yourself with the task.

Press the button below to proceed.

The next 3 trials you will complete are practice trials.
The feedback you receive on the display when the F key is tapped will be the same as in the next block of trials that you will complete.

Attempt to finish the trial with the top of the red bar within the target area.

  • Do not tap the F key until the GO! appears
  • Do not release the A, W, E, Spacebar, Right Arrow until prompted.
You will now answer a few questions. Press the button below to proceed.
